This paper deals with wireless networks and their performance under certain policies. The focus is on the delivery ratio and hard deadline constraints. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a framework and policies based on debt, which may fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Machine Learning (cs.MA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses performance bounds, which may relate to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
